%% Decorators stack. Each one wraps the previous and forwards calls
%% through its own logic. The order often matters: buffering outside
%% a slow source; encryption inside a transport; logging closest to
%% the underlying call.
flowchart LR
    File[File] --> Gz[GzipDecoder&lt;File&gt;]
    Gz --> Buf[BufReader&lt;GzipDecoder&lt;File&gt;&gt;]
    Buf --> Log[LoggingReader&lt;...&gt;]
    Log --> App[App: read bytes]

    note1["Each wrapper is generic over its inner type.<br/>Composition happens at compile time;<br/>the whole stack is monomorphized and inlined."]
    Buf -.-> note1
